To find $f^{-1}(33)$, we need to find the value of $x$ such that $f(x)=33$. 

We can start by setting $f(x)=33$ and solving for $x$. 

\begin{align*}
4x^3+1&=33 \\
4x^3&=32 \\
x^3&=8 \\
\end{align*}

To simplify this further, we can take the cube root of both sides of the equation:

\begin{align*}
\sqrt[3]{x^3}&=\sqrt[3]{8} \\
x&=2
\end{align*}

Therefore, $f^{-1}(33)=\boxed{2}$.

